Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, sprinkle over half the @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1%sachet},
then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop half the @garlic cloves{3}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{}
with a drizzle of oil and scrunch to enclose it. Roast the parcel on the chip
baking tray until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

In the meantime, peel and grate the remaining garlic.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%g}.

Drain and rinse the @Mixed Beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the garlic and remaining Mexican style spice mix. Fry until
fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%g}, mixed beans,
@Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}. Simmer until thickened,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and stir in the @Butter{20%g} until melted. Season with
salt and pepper.

In the meantime, in a #medium bowl{}, mix together the @Mayonnaise{32%g} and
@Coleslaw Mix{120%g}. Season with salt and pepper.

Once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the
skin and mash with a #fork{}, then stir into the coleslaw mix.

Set your slaw aside for later.

Just before you're ready to serve, slice the @Brioche Hot Dog Buns{2} top down
through the middle (but not all the way through).

Pop the buns into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, reheat the chilli if needed.

Share the buns between your serving plates, then fill with your bean chilli.

Sprinkle over the grated Cheddar and @Crispy Onions{1%sachet} to finish.

Serve with the spiced chips and slaw alongside. Enjoy!